mployees are active in the community schools and local charitable organizations  alon’s commitment to education has enabled the big spring school district to build the alon technology center where teachers and students receive training and conduct workshops  our refinery has also been awarded the employer excellence award from the texas workforce development board for being an exemplary employer and for contributions toward local development and corporate citizenship we support numerous local charitable organizations and community events such as alon usa and alon brands funtastic fourth big spring cowboy reunion and rodeo big spring isd forsan isd and coahoma isd boys and girls club of big spring big spring state hospital howard college heritage museum pops in the park relay for life salvation army angel tree program united way of big spring and howard county us national hang gliding competition west texas centers hoops dreams and goals  these are only a few of the important causes that alon and the refinery employees support in big spring and howard county  we are proud to live in and be a part of the west texas community home about refining asphalt retailbranded marketing investors contact delek us  commerce way brentwood tn     alon usa terms of use  privacy policy  legal historical data  alon usa energy inc disclaimer links to thirdparty websites are provided solely as a convenience to you by following the link below you will be taken to an independent web site that is not maintained by alon we do not endorse or make any representations as to the accuracy or completeness of any information product or materials contained in any of these sites if you decide to access any of the thirdparty sites linked to our web site you do so entirely at your own risk accept terms continue skip to main content contact news home about corporate officers community relations safety and environmental careers corporate structure refining big spring refinery california refineries krotz