an  convenience stores in texas and new mexico in july  delek us holdings purchased alon usa in an allstock transaction contents  expansion  merger with delek us  refinery explosion  references  external links expansionedit alon usa announced it would buy paramount petroleum corp for  million cash and assume  million in debt the deal closed in august  alon usa also plans to buy the assets of edgington oil co for  million cash a deal delayed in closing due to an ftc request for further information among paramounts assets are a  barrels per day  md refinery in paramount california and seven asphalt terminals edgington is a topping refinery located in long beach california with a listed capacity of about  barrels per day  md in july  alon usa closed on the transaction to purchase  convenience stores from good time stores in march  alon usa announced that it would purchase abilene based skinnys convenience stores for  million dollars in may  valero announced they had sold the  bpd krotz springs louisiana refinery to alon usa for  million on june   alon announced that it has completed the acquisition of the bakersfield california refinery from big west of california llc a subsidiary of flying j inc the purchase price of the bakersfield transaction including substantially all of the assets of big west consists of  million in cash the company also acquired the bakersfield refinerys existing inventory as of the closing date of the transaction the bakersfield refinery is located in californias central valley and has the capacity to refine up to  barrels per day of crude oil the refinery is supplied by crude oil produced in the san joaquin valley with its products marketed in california and is a major provider of motor fuels in central california merger with delek usedit on july   delek us holdings inc brentwood tenn completed its purchase of alon israel oil co ltd’s usbased refining and marketing subsidiary alon usa energy incas part of the allstock transaction delek acquired the remaining  of alon usa’s common stock not already owned by delek the combined company will be led primarily by delek us’ existing management team refinery explosionedit on february   an explosion occurred at an oil refinery in big spring texas owned by alon usa the plant employs about  employees and has a capacity of  barrels  m of oil a day this event has caused portions of interstate  to be shut down initial reports state that four workers were injured in addition to the four workers a passing motorist on interstate  sustained an injury when debris struck her vehicle according to local reports according to a press release by the company on february  the explosion occurred in the area around the propylene splitter unit although the cause has not yet been determined information on the companys website states that alon usa acquired ownership of the big spring texas refinery in august  when alon israel oil company ltd purchased the us fuels marketing and refining assets of atofina petrochemicals inc fina the refinery has been in service for more than  years and produces fuel products and asphalt for the southwestern united states it was constructed in  by the original owner joshua cosden referencesedit  a b c alon usa energy alj annual sec income statement filing via wikinvest  a b alon usa energy alj annual sec balance sheet filing via wikinvest  delek us alon usa complete merger oilgas journal  july    west texas refinery explodes associated press  february    miracle on i  injured in huge explosion big spring herald  february  check date values in date help  alon usa provides additional information regarding the explosion at the big spring refinery alon usa  february   external linksedit dallas portal companies portal energy portal alon usa corporate site alon executive says change is on the horizon bic magazine interview with jeff morris may  alon israel oil company corporate site retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlealonusaoldid categories compan