each and bakersfield california collectively known as the california refineries as well as a light crude oil refinery in krotz springs louisiana alon was a leading marketer of asphalt which it distributes primarily through asphalt terminals located predominately in the southwestern and western united states alon brands inc the retail and branded marketing subsidiary of alon usa marketed and supplied alon motor fuels to independent and companyowned retail locations alon brands was the largest licensee of eleven in the us operating more than  convenience stores in texas and new mexico in july  delek us holdings purchased alon usa in an allstock transaction contents  expansion  merger with delek us  refinery explosion  references  external links expansionedit alon usa announced it would buy paramount petroleum corp for  million cash and assume  million in debt the deal closed in august  alon usa also plans to buy the assets of edgington oil co for  million cash a deal delayed in closing due to an ftc request for further information among paramounts assets are a  barrels per day  md refinery in paramount california and seven asphalt terminals edgington is a topping refinery located in long beach california with a listed capacity of about  barrels per day  md in july  alon usa closed on the transaction to purchase  convenience stores from good time stores in march  alon usa announced that it would purchase abilene based skinnys convenience stores for  million dollars in may  valero announced they had sold the  bpd krotz springs louisiana refinery to alon usa for  million on june   alon announced that it has completed the acquisition of the bakersfield california refinery from big west of california llc a subsidiary of flying j inc the purchase price of the bakersfield transaction including substantially all of the assets of big west consists of  million in cash the company also acquired the bakersfield refinerys existing inventory as of the closing date of the transactio